Runed Fighters Staff 19/20 - 20k - no longer drops<br>
Imbued Fighters Staff 38/40 - 10k - replaced RFS.<br>
<br>
<br>
Having used both, and currently owning an RFS, I'm completely torn. I just can't decide on what one I want.<br>
I think, especially on Monk boards, that this topic has been stabbed to death, and the center of much contraversy. So anyone with any monk experience in these 2hb areas, help me decide!!<br>
<br>
They're both 1.05 in ratio. IFS gives the nice old hits of 150, the taunt is low (well, not really low, but compared to RFS), it's light at 4wt, and just an incredible weapon, and definately cheap for its ratio.<br>
On the other hand, RFS is insanely fast, hitting twice as more as the IFS, haste item or not. It's hits range from 50 - 60 at my lvl (40), and it's just really a non-stop swinger, although at 6wt can be a STA drain with haste. However, it is a killer for taunt, and on DS mobs, really tears me up.<br>
<br>
Anyone have a personal favourite? Recommendations?<br>
I miss my double 150's with the IFS, but the RFS im doing noticabley more damage, seen as the hits land more often. IFS misses really hurt.<br>
