<br>
For a Paladin, the debate was to use the Arbitor's Combine Greatsword or Ornate Rune Blade. Both are 2hs, but with different ratios.<br>
<br>
ACG: 30/43 +15 wis, +25 mana<br>
ORB: 19/30 +5 AC +3 all saves<br>
<br>
According to Copeland's Weapon Analyzer, they're roughly equivalent in terms of DPM, with the ORB pulling slightly ahead at level 50+. Now, my personal preference was to use the ACG because I liked the big hits and the extra mana never hurt. But, when fighting red mobs (like on raids) you tend to miss a lot more and hit for mean damage instead of max damage more often. So in this case, the ORB is more efficient.<br>
<br>
<br>
